ed to Italy to play for FC Internazionale MilanoAmbrosiana now Inter Milan until 1936 During this period he represented the Italy national football team twice when the nationality rules were less strict than they now are He later returned to Uruguay to play for CA Pearol from 1936 to 1940By the time of his death in July 1984 at the age of 76 he was the last surviving member of Uruguays 1930 World Cup winning team though it would be another 26 years before the death of the Francisco Varallolast surviving participant of that World Cuprefhttpwwwbbccouknewsworldlatinamerica11134965 Last surviving player from first World Cup final dies BBC News 31 Aug 2010 22 March 2011ref